  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Coton de Tulear in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Coton de Tulear is named on the HDB-approved breed list, so you can keep one in an HDB flat. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and at 3.5 to 6 kg the Coton sits comfortably inside the small-breed rules. Every Coton we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase, so the paperwork is handled for you."
      bridge="Is a Coton de Tulear HDB-approved? Yes, by name on the list, a pleasant surprise for a breed this rare. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
